column2: Kawasaki Mule Trans Metal Top
column3:
One-Piece Kawasaki Mule Trans metal roof by Ranch Armor is one-of-a-kind. The Mule Trans is unique because it has this really cool feature that allows you to fold the back seat forward and extend the cargo bed capacity. Reminds us of a transformer in a simple functional kind-of-way. The issue is there isn't a top that can support the dump bed and its headache rack that needs to go up and somewhere (hitting your top if you have ANY OTHER but ours) when the bed is tilted/dumped. We believe the RanchArmor brand and line of roofs should always be functional and tough as nails. We created an optional door that opens on super heavy-duty hinges and allows easy use of the dump bed while still having a bad ass metal utility top. Coolest part about our trap door is it blends right in with the top, you hardly know it's even there!¬†

We know you bought the Mule to work, it's one of the best UTV's for day-to-day rugged activities. The thought of even the slightest noise coming from this metal roof annoyed us, so we tested and designed the dump bed trap door specifically around a ZERO TOLERANCE noise policy we have for all of our tops. So, just to be clear... This roof like all of our others makes NO NOISE.¬†

KAWASAKI MULE TRANS 3010/4010 ONE-PIECE METAL ROOF CREW SPECS:

¬†

  • Steel Construction with steel tubular/Angle Iron sub-frame
  • Textured Powder Coat standard
  • 14 Gauge Steel Shell (Optional 11 Gauge Aluminum Upgrade)
  • Rain ‚ÄúGutters‚Äù Front & Rear
  • Direct fitment using factory holes. Easily bolts on using 4 bolts with no modification.¬†
  • Lifetime Warranty on construction

¬†

  • Have full size doors? OR plan to put on full size doors? - Make sure you let us know you need "LOW PROFILE FLANGES" - in the Comment section at checkout or contact us directly to order.¬†

column2: Polaris Ranger 570/800 Crew Metal Top
column3:
The Polaris Ranger 570/800 Crew metal one-piece utility top is the most rugged on the market. The 2011+ Rangers were a huge turning point for the UTV market. This is when they really started to become machines that were serving more needs in the recreational fields than ever before. Our first metal roofs were for this specific model, and it's what started it all in terms of tops for us. We take great pride in going the extra mile and mandate a ZERO TOLERANCE noise policy, meaning absolutely NO rattling! We also know the tops now have huge storage capability so standing on it shouldn't be nerve racking. Our tops will easily support one thousand pounds without hesitation, or in this case flexing and popping.¬†

Our one-piece tops for the Polaris Ranger 570/800 Crew utilize 14¬†gauge¬†sheet metal that has been laser-cut, and pressed to form a nice solid shell. We then weld the sub-frame that is made specifically¬†for the 570/800 crew to the shell.¬†

Polaris Ranger 570/800 Crew Full-Size Metal Roof Crew Specs:

  • Steel Construction with steel tubular/Angle Iron sub-frame
  • Textured Powder Coat standard
  • 14 Gauge Steel Shell (Optional 11 Gauge Aluminum Upgrade)
  • Rain ‚ÄúGutters‚Äù Front & Rear
  • U-Clamp Hardware for easy installation. (Set the roof in place over the roll bar and fasten the U-Clamps on the pre-set studs from the bottom)
  • Lifetime Warranty on construction

POLARIS RANGER 570/800 Crew ONE-PIECE METAL ROOF COMPATIBILITY:

  • 100% compatible with all: 2011-2022 model Polaris Ranger Crew 570/800 Pipe Frame
    • Have full size doors? OR plan to put on full size doors? - Make sure you let us know you need "LOW PROFILE FLANGES" - in the Comment section at checkout or contact us directly to order.¬†

column2: Polaris Ranger Full-Size Single Cab Metal Top (Pipe Frame 08-20)
column3:
New re-designed Ranch Armor Polaris Ranger Single Cab Metal Roof is here! No other metal top for the single cab UTV's comes close! It's sleek, bold, built with pride and quality at the highest standard.

We are one of the few companies who actively carries Polaris Ranger metal tops for 2002-2008. Of course we carry roof for 2009-2020 Single Cab Polaris Ranger UTV's.¬†When checking out or contacting us to order, please be sure to verify your year/model Ranger so we can assure fitment. This is a full-size metal top, we periodically throughout the year do runs for mid-size models, please contact us if you have ANY questions in regards to tops for mid-size model Rangers.

Roof shown in pictures may NOT be a standard equipped roof. Options and items such as: light bars, and light bar cages are available at additional cost(s).¬†

Polaris Ranger Single Cab Specifications:

  • Sheet metal "Roof Shell" constructed of 14 guage steel
  • 14 Guage 1 inch steel tube/channel mix sub-frame construction. The "skeleton" that the sheet metal is welded to that actually mounts to the UTV.¬†
  • All sheet metal is 100% laser-cut for a smooth edge. No rough notches or indentions seen with water-jet/plasma cutting techniques.¬†
  • Semi-Gloss Moderate Textured Powder Coat is standard. We also offer bed-liner and a more rugged wrinkle powder coat that is slightly more expensive then the standard semi-gloss powder finish.¬†
  • Front and Side Rails (Utlity Rack) Standard - constructed of 1 inch 14 guage steel tubing
  • 1 inch tall Rain ‚ÄúGutters‚Äù Front & Rear. This is a big deal! Keeps water/rain from hitting your legs and knees. Water is routed out sides away from passengers.
  • U-Clamp Hardware for easy installation.¬†NEWER Ranger's (900 Singles and 570 Full-size Singles) mount using 4 slotted holes that fasten roof via the sub-frame to the factory overhead lock-and-ride holes on Polaris. NO MODIFICATION NEEDED!
  • No modification, mounts perfectly to OEM Polaris frame
  • Lifetime Warranty on construction of metal. No warranty on any coatings.¬†

POLARIS RANGER Full-size single cab ROOF COMPATIBILITY:

  • 100% compatible with all: 2002-2020 model Polaris Ranger 700-800 Pipe-Frames
    • Have full size doors? OR plan to put on full size doors? - Make sure you let us know you need "LOW PROFILE FLANGES" - in the Comment section at checkout or contact us directly to order.¬†
